# Problem Solving with AI Unit Overview
 
#### Teachers can use the Problem Solving with AI Unit as part of the AI Foundations course, or as a standalone resource for grades 9-12. It can also be integrated into existing computer science, math, or science curricula, offering scheduling flexibility.

<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; background: #f7f8fa; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); font-family: Figtree, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 800px; margin: 20px auto;">

  <div>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 0; font-weight: bold;">Students will:</h4>
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14pt">
      <li>Investigate how AI generates responses.</li>
      <li>Critically evaluate AI-generated outputs.</li>
      <li>Refine AI-generated content.</li>
      <li>Explore AI's role in creativity, forecasting, and decision-making.</li>
		<li>Design and test AI-assisted solutions to real-world challenges.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <img src="https://images.code.org/98317ca257f4e6677d2a59cfe7f680a9-Screenshot 2025-05-19 at 3.34.21 PM.png" 
         alt="Icon with computer and data symbols" 
         style="border-radius: 10px; width: 200px; height: auto;">
  </div>
</div>

## Unit Calendar 

#### Take a quick look at the lessons included in this unit using the calendar tool.

#### This version of the calendar shows the pacing for 45 minute class periods and can be customized using the drop-down menu to accommodate your schedule. 

